Western Cape police are investigating a case of murder after a woman was shot dead during an alleged business robbery at a Shoprite in Zwelethema, Worcester on Sunday. Police spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana said the 55-year-old woman was fatally wounded around 06:00. "Three armed unidentified suspects perpetrated a business robbery and shot the victim. Police detectives are on the scene combing for clued in order to arrest the perpetrators." SOURCE:NEWS24